- `styles/main.css`: `.conv-section`, `.conv-section__header/intro`, `.conv-cooldown` (amber), `.conv-rows/.conv-row` (flex card per conversion), `.conv-from/.conv-arrow/.conv-to`, `.btn--convert` (blue gradient), `.conv-total`, plus `@media вЙ§480px` column layout.

**Architecture decisions:**
- T163 applies the buff at the per-unit level inside the attack summation loop, so it only amplifies that unit type's contribution вАФ other multipliers (techs, formation, morale, etc.) still apply globally on top.
- T164 uses a circular chain so every resource has exactly one conversion target, keeping the UI simple. The 30s cooldown (120 ticks) prevents spam-converting and makes the Workshop a deliberate tactical choice rather than an automation tool.
- Workshop is unique (max 1) to maintain scarcity. No tick system needed вАФ conversion is purely player-triggered with a cooldown enforced by `state.conversions.cooldownUntil`.
- Save version bumped to 49 for the new `conversions` state field.

