- The upgrade requires Iron Age (not just tech) to create a natural gating point that matches the mid-to-late game power curve.
- Citizen roles persist across New Game (like formation and archetype) because they represent player playstyle preferences, not per-game progression. `state.citizenRoles = null` is initialised lazily on first `adjustCitizenRole()` call.
- Workers apply a multiplicative bonus to all positive rates after all other bonuses (including weather, season, policy, mastery) вАФ this makes workers feel powerful in a developed economy where many bonuses stack. Capped at 50% max reduction for scholars and soldiers to prevent degenerate strategies.
- The `maxSlots = floor(pop/100)` formula means the first slot requires 100 citizens вАФ players must invest in houses and food production to unlock citizen roles, creating meaningful build order decisions.

