**Architecture decisions:**
- Crisis penalties are pushed directly to `state.randomEvents.activeModifiers` (same format as disaster modifiers) so they integrate seamlessly with the existing `recalcRates()` penalty system, including the Grand Cathedral wonder's halving of disaster severity.
- Crisis spawning is blocked until at least one game-tick cycle after boot/load (nextCrisisTick is set ahead by _nextInterval() in initCrises), so players aren't immediately hit with a crisis at game start.
- The crisis banner uses DOM-based innerHTML re-render (not a full panel system) since it's a transient overlay вАФ the delegated click listener on the parent div survives innerHTML updates.
- Hero legacy bonuses are computed once at enshrinement time and stored as a simple `{resвЖТval}` rates object вАФ avoids re-evaluating skill chains on every tick and makes saved data human-readable.
- LEGACY_RATES_BY_SKILL converts ALL 10 skills to resource rate bonuses (not just the 4 that already give rates), so no skill choice leaves a hero with zero legacy value. Combat-oriented skills convert to gold income (tribute/glory), training/research skills to iron/mana.
