**T140 вАФ Population Happiness System:**

**Files modified:**
- `game/src/systems/population.js`: Added `HAPPY_HIGH = 75` and `HAPPY_LOW = 25` exports; imported `recalcRates` from `resources.js`; `initPopulation()` now sets `state.population.happiness = 50` and migrates older saves. Added `getHappiness()` getter. Added `happinessTick()` вАФ derives target happiness from food ratio (вЙ•60% вЖТ +20, <25% вЖТ вИТ25), morale (вЙ•70 вЖТ +15, <30 вЖТ вИТ15), and active crises (вИТ15), then drifts `state.population.happiness` at 0.2%/tick toward the target. Calls `recalcRates()`, emits `POPULATION_CHANGED`, and logs a message when happiness crosses the 75/25 thresholds.
- `game/src/systems/resources.js`: In `recalcRates()`, after the T134 scholar block and before `Object.assign(state.rates, rates)`, reads `state.population?.happiness` directly (no import needed) and applies `√Ч1.10` to all positive rates when вЙ• 75 (Prosperous) or `√Ч0.90` when вЙ§ 25 (Unrest).
- `game/src/main.js`: Added `happinessTick` to the population.js import; `registerSystem(happinessTick)` added after `populationTick` in `boot()`.
- `game/src/ui/hud.js`: Added `getHappiness, HAPPY_HIGH, HAPPY_LOW` to the population.js import. `_renderPopBadge()` now appends a mood emoji (рЯШК / рЯШР / рЯШ§), shows happiness % in the tooltip with the active effect label, and toggles `.population-badge--happy` (green) / `.population-badge--unrest` (red) CSS classes.
- `game/styles/main.css`: `.population-badge--happy` (green accent) and `.population-badge--unrest` (red accent) modifier classes.

**Architecture decisions:**
- Happiness drift rate (0.2%/tick = 0.8%/s) means transitions take ~30-60 seconds вАФ long enough to feel meaningful but fast enough to respond to player actions.
- `recalcRates()` is imported directly into population.js; resources.js reads `state.population.happiness` from state (no import back), avoiding circular dependency.
- The happiness modifier is applied last in `recalcRates()` so it acts as a global multiplier on the final calculated rates, stacking cleanly with all other modifiers.
- Save/load: `state.population` is already serialized as a whole object in `_save()`, so `happiness` is automatically persisted. Older saves are migrated in `initPopulation()`.

